Class Literal<X>

  • java.lang.Object
    • objenome.op.Node<Void,X>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BooleanERC, Doubliteral, IntegerERC, Scalar

    public class Literal<X>
extends Node<Void,X>
    Literal values are terminal nodes with a specific value. Typically the value of a literal will not change.
    Since:
    2.0
    See Also:
    Variable

        public java.lang.Class dataType(java.lang.Class... inputTypes)

        public Literal clone()
        Creates a new Literal instance which is a copy of this instance. The clone will contain a value which is a reference to the same object as this literal's value. For mutable object values, users should consider extending this class to provide a clone method which can provide an appropriate deep clone.
